body_html:
@jakiechris I had this problem as well!

I had /usr/bin/gcc symlinked to a homebrew installation /usr/local/bin/gcc which was gcc4.9. The homebrew distribution of gcc threw the same error you're getting.

I fixed this by unlinking the brew installation from /usr/local/bin/gcc and kept the clang that is originally installed on macOS Sierra (/usr/bin/gcc).

$ gcc --version
Configured with: --prefix=/Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer/usr --with-gxx-include-dir=/usr/include/c++/4.2.1
Apple LLVM version 8.1.0 (clang-802.0.42)
Target: x86_64-apple-darwin16.0.0
Thread model: posix
InstalledDir: /Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer/Toolchains/XcodeDefault.xctoolchain/usr/bin

Note: It may be necessary, but not recommended to use

$ sudo tensorflow/contrib/makefile/build_all_ios.sh

body:
@jakiechris I had this problem as well!

I had `/usr/bin/gcc` symlinked to a `homebrew` installation `/usr/local/bin/gcc` which was `gcc4.9`. The `homebrew` distribution of `gcc` threw the same error you're getting. 

I fixed this by unlinking the `brew` installation from `/usr/local/bin/gcc` and kept the `clang` that is originally installed on **macOS Sierra**  (`/usr/bin/gcc`).

```sh
$ gcc --version
Configured with: --prefix=/Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer/usr --with-gxx-include-dir=/usr/include/c++/4.2.1
Apple LLVM version 8.1.0 (clang-802.0.42)
Target: x86_64-apple-darwin16.0.0
Thread model: posix
InstalledDir: /Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer/Toolchains/XcodeDefault.xctoolchain/usr/bin
```

**Note:** It may be necessary, but not recommended to use
```sh
$ sudo tensorflow/contrib/makefile/build_all_ios.sh
```
